description:
&lt;p&gt;A full time vacancy exists for a Healthcare Support Worker on Pearce ward . You will work as part of a friendly and caring team on the busy Cystic Fibrosis ward. You will undertake the role of caring for patients through indirect supervision by a professionally qualified nurse. Flexibility is essential as the successful candidate will work long days, early, late or night shifts.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Manchester University Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust (MFT), our Healthcare Support Workers take great pride in the essential work we do. That’s because we’re not just helping patients, we’re going the extra mile for them – day in, day out. But more than that, our team’s commitment to work with empathy, consideration and dignity means that we’re among the best – and most compassionate – in our field.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will need to have:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Level 2 NVQ/Apprenticeship in Health and Care&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication skills – in particular listening skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A friendly, open, empathetic and compassionate communication style&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A strong ability to engage with patients, visitors and colleagues&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The ability to work well in a team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameAnn Bowling Charlotte RourkeJob titleWard ManagerEmail addressann.bowling@mft.nhs.ukTelephone number01612915315Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ward Manager : Ann Bowling or Charlotte Rourke&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ward contact number : 016 291 5315&lt;/p&gt;
